inputs.description: A collection of arguments for invoking getDevEnvironment.

envId.description: - (Required) The system-generated unique ID of the Dev Environment for which you want to view information. To retrieve a list of Dev Environment IDs, use [ListDevEnvironments](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/codecatalyst/latest/APIReference/API_ListDevEnvironments.html).

projectName.description: The name of the project in the space.

outputs.description: A collection of values returned by getDevEnvironment.

alias.description: The user-specified alias for the Dev Environment.

creatorId.description: The system-generated unique ID of the user who created the Dev Environment.

id.description: The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.

ides.description: Information about the integrated development environment (IDE) configured for a Dev Environment.

inactivityTimeoutMinutes.description: The amount of time the Dev Environment will run without any activity detected before stopping, in minutes. Only whole integers are allowed. Dev Environments consume compute minutes when running.

instanceType.description: The Amazon EC2 instace type to use for the Dev Environment.

lastUpdatedTime.description: The time when the Dev Environment was last updated, in coordinated universal time (UTC) timestamp format as specified in [RFC 3339](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc3339#section-5.6).

persistentStorages.description: Information about the amount of storage allocated to the Dev Environment.

repositories.description: The source repository that contains the branch to clone into the Dev Environment.

status.description: The current status of the Dev Environment. From: PENDING | RUNNING | STARTING | STOPPING | STOPPED | FAILED | DELETING | DELETED.
